New Records: Devon Conway scored a peerless 92 from 58 balls
Key Match Events: Finn Allen took on Patrick Cummins, Mitchell Starc, and Josh Hazlewood within the first three overs
David Warner edged Trent Boult for a boundary before deflecting a Tim Southee delivery onto his stumps
Aaron Finch and Mitchell Marsh threatened for a moment, but New Zealand's left-arm spinner Mitchell Santner had Finch caught at cover and Marsh lifted Southee to James Neesham at deep midwicket
New Zealand's left-arm spinner Mitchell Santner had Finn Stoinis caught at deep cover by an airborne Glenn Phillips
Post-Match Reflections: Devon Conway said, 'It was pretty special. I've seen [Allen] do it time and time again. He's fearless, and credit has to go to him. The way Finn plays his game complements my game, I knew that I could just play my game and bat around him.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: New Zealand laid into Australia with an extra level of ferocity, racking up 200 for the cost of only three wickets
Australia generally fancy chasing big totals, but it has to start from the top
In a group stage where only two teams will progress to the knockout phase, New Zealand now have the upper hand, and Australia finding a way to beat the English favourites is now vital
